{"word":"τυλόω","slug":"τυλόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τυλόω</b></el> <el>(τῠλόω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ώσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τύλος'><el>τύλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make knobby</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ρόπαλα σιδήρῳ τετυλωμένα</el> clubs <i>knobbed</i> with iron, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to make callous</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be callous</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}